I've carried this stuff a lot of times.

879
01:13:50,120 --> 01:13:55,319
Where? Up the escalator at Bloomington's,
or Bloomingberg's, or wherever it is?

880
01:13:55,440 --> 01:13:59,194
Bloomingdale's. And what the hell
do you know about New York?

881
01:13:59,760 --> 01:14:02,035
Ever hear of the Madison Square Gardens?

882
01:14:02,160 --> 01:14:02,831
No.

883
01:14:02,960 --> 01:14:06,635
They got a rodeo there, and it's
a damn big thing. And I've been in it.

884
01:14:06,760 --> 01:14:09,320
Well, I've been to the rodeo. Twice.

885
01:14:13,160 --> 01:14:15,276
Did you stay
for the rattlesnake roundup?

886
01:14:15,400 --> 01:14:17,755
Yes. I stayed right to the end.
I saw the whole thing.

887
01:14:17,880 --> 01:14:21,350
They don't have one. How are you
gonna round up a rattlesnake?

888
01:14:21,480 --> 01:14:25,519
Oh, God. I'm just trying to be pleasant.
You get so worked up about everything.

889
01:14:25,640 --> 01:14:28,996
What have I got to be worked up about?
I've only got a stole horse...

890
01:14:29,120 --> 01:14:33,830
...everybody but the Coast Guard after me,
and now I'm carryin' a crazy woman...

891
01:14:33,960 --> 01:14:38,988
...wearin' shoes from Bloomingberg's, that
thinks she's seen a rattlesnake roundup.

892
01:14:41,320 --> 01:14:44,630
Go on, pick it up if you're takin' it.
Only it ain't goin' on my horse.

893
01:14:44,760 --> 01:14:46,990
Your horse

894
01:14:53,400 --> 01:14:56,949
Ahh... Here, give me
those glasses, would you?

895
01:14:57,200 --> 01:14:59,350
They're prescription.

896
01:14:59,960 --> 01:15:03,077
You wait here with him
till I get back, ya hear?

897
01:15:03,520 --> 01:15:06,114
But if you're spotted
and you don't come back...

898
01:15:06,240 --> 01:15:08,037
Call your lawyer.

899
01:15:14,400 --> 01:15:16,072
Hello. Can I help you?

900
01:15:16,200 --> 01:15:18,236
Howdy. Uh...

901
01:15:18,360 --> 01:15:24,390
Well, uh, I'm broke down the road apiece,
and I wondered if I could use your phone...

902
01:15:24,520 --> 01:15:29,594
I got a friend in Mesquite, and he's in
a bit of trouble, so I need to use a phone.

903
01:15:29,720 --> 01:15:33,713
I'd be obliged if I could use yours.
Happy to pay you for it.

904
01:15:33,840 --> 01:15:38,197
- We got a phone. Come on in.
- Oh. Great. Appreci... Appreciate it.

905
01:15:40,200 --> 01:15:42,953
Phone's right there. You help yourself.

906
01:15:44,800 --> 01:15:46,756
Thank you.

907
01:16:10,600 --> 01:16:13,160
- Hello?
- <i>Gus, it's Sonny</i>.

908
01:16:13,280 --> 01:16:14,269
Sonny!

909
01:16:14,400 --> 01:16:16,994
I gotta talk to you.
I can't talk long. Now listen...

910
01:16:17,120 --> 01:16:19,793
- <i>Sonny!</i>
- Gus, please, just listen real careful.

911
01:16:19,920 --> 01:16:23,071
- I'm in the kitchen.
- <i>People are gonna come, probably police</i>.

912
01:16:23,200 --> 01:16:26,909
They're gonna ask you about the camper.
I want you to tell 'em I stole it.

913
01:16:27,040 --> 01:16:29,554
Say it, Gus. "Sonny stole the camper."

914
01:16:29,680 --> 01:16:32,478
My Wild Blue Yonder? I bought it in Elko.

915
01:16:32,600 --> 01:16:36,718
No, Gus. I bought it for you, remember?
And I'll buy you a nice new one.

916
01:16:36,840 --> 01:16:40,913
When the people ask about the camper,
tell them "Sonny stole the camper."

917
01:16:41,040 --> 01:16:43,873
Try to remember it.
I'll see ya, friend. I gotta go.

918
01:16:47,480 --> 01:16:49,311
Oh, uh...

919
01:16:49,440 --> 01:16:52,557
Partner, I'm much obliged
for the use of that phone.

920
01:16:52,680 --> 01:16:55,274
Here. Five oughta cover it.

921
01:16:55,400 --> 01:16:57,356
Mr Steele...

922
01:17:00,520 --> 01:17:02,988
...I don't want your money.

923
01:17:03,120 --> 01:17:05,554
I saw you on the television.
You and the horse.

924
01:17:05,680 --> 01:17:09,070
I want you to know
I'd be proud to help you any way I can.

925
01:17:09,200 --> 01:17:13,034
Right now, it looks like
we oughta get you out of this county.

926
01:17:24,600 --> 01:17:26,352
How do you like it so far?

927
01:17:37,320 --> 01:17:39,834
Edwin. How's the day? Treatin' you good?

928
01:17:39,960 --> 01:17:43,919
Doin' all right. Got the whole worid
lookin' for that cowboy.

929
01:17:44,040 --> 01:17:48,636
He's probably over that mountain by now.
I'd go take a nap on my porch.

930
01:17:48,760 --> 01:17:51,672
I wouldn't wanna find him anyway -
except for that reward.

931
01:17:52,040 --> 01:17:54,235
50,000 bucks is a mound of cash.

932
01:17:55,720 --> 01:17:57,836
I wouldn't get my hopes up.

933
01:18:42,960 --> 01:18:45,713
All right, you're clear. Come on down.

934
01:19:00,240 --> 01:19:05,155
I don't know where you're headed, but
Escalante's six miles over that mountain.

935
01:19:05,280 --> 01:19:10,434
The woman put together some stuff -
bread and cake and stew and coffee.

936
01:19:10,560 --> 01:19:12,949
I put a bottle in there
to keep your blood pumpin'.

937
01:19:13,080 --> 01:19:15,150
- I sure do thank you.
- Ain't no need to.

938
01:19:15,280 --> 01:19:19,478
Listen, there's not many people
you'd trust $50,000 worth.

939
01:19:20,280 --> 01:19:24,512
You better get on over the mountain
'fore it comes to me what I'm passin' up.

940
01:19:26,600 --> 01:19:28,556
Come on.

941
01:19:31,840 --> 01:19:33,796
Oh, my God!

942
01:19:36,560 --> 01:19:38,949
- Can we rest a little?
- Not yet.

943
01:19:40,160 --> 01:19:44,358
- Where the hell are we?
- Well, not in jail, look at it that way.

944
01:19:45,880 --> 01:19:48,269
- I can't go any farther.
- Oh, sure you can.

945
01:19:48,400 --> 01:19:53,997
Hell, I've known people go through stuff.
I knew a guy... misjudged a Brahma once.

946
01:19:54,120 --> 01:19:58,830
Put his rib through his right lung,
the guy could hardly breathe...

947
01:19:59,480 --> 01:20:02,756
He still got up and rode
the rankest mare there.

948
01:20:03,840 --> 01:20:09,233
I will never understand why you find
that kind of behaviour admirable.

949
01:20:09,360 --> 01:20:12,830
- Gets you up the hill.
- I have to rest... for a minute.

950
01:20:15,000 --> 01:20:17,036
Hey, Steele?

951
01:20:17,160 --> 01:20:18,991
Sonny?

952
01:20:19,120 --> 01:20:21,554
Norman!

953
01:20:25,520 --> 01:20:27,750
How do you know "Norman"?

954
01:20:28,280 --> 01:20:30,635
I never divulge sources.

955
01:20:31,960 --> 01:20:35,509
"Divulge sources"..."Divulge sources"...

956
01:20:36,960 --> 01:20:40,919
Here, get up. Come on.
You sure do your homework, don't you?

957
01:20:44,360 --> 01:20:47,557
Try to put your mind on somethin' else,
make things easier.

958
01:20:48,040 --> 01:20:50,349
Get it off your feet.

959
01:20:51,680 --> 01:20:53,671
Do you know "The Star-Spangled Banner"?

960
01:20:53,800 --> 01:20:55,711
- What?!
- The national anthem?

961
01:20:55,840 --> 01:21:00,391
I know it's the national anthem.
You mean can I sing it? It's hard to sing.

962
01:21:00,520 --> 01:21:03,273
Yeah, it is. Why do you suppose that is?

963
01:21:03,880 --> 01:21:07,998
Hey, that's a very interesting question.
Why don't we sit down and discuss it?

964
01:21:08,120 --> 01:21:10,509
I used to be a psychology major.

965
01:21:10,640 --> 01:21:13,837
"America the Beautiful",
that's an easy tune to carry.

966
01:21:13,960 --> 01:21:16,633
Why don't we sit down
and sing it together?

967
01:21:16,760 --> 01:21:18,716
# O spa...

968
01:21:19,680 --> 01:21:23,116
# O beautiful for spacious skies

969
01:21:23,800 --> 01:21:26,268
# With amber waves of grain

970
01:21:26,400 --> 01:21:28,914
- Come on. Come on, sing it.
- Oh, God!

971
01:21:29,040 --> 01:21:33,670
# For purple mountains majesty

972
01:21:33,800 --> 01:21:38,715
# Above the fruited plain

973
01:21:39,200 --> 01:21:44,638
# America, America...

974
01:22:08,040 --> 01:22:10,349
Halloween.

975
01:22:10,920 --> 01:22:12,592
Ha...

976
01:22:13,600 --> 01:22:15,750
Hal-louise?

977
01:22:16,360 --> 01:22:18,920
- What?
- Your name: Hallie.

978
01:22:19,920 --> 01:22:22,150
That's not your name.

979
01:22:24,160 --> 01:22:26,116
Alice.

980
01:22:26,560 --> 01:22:28,278
My name is Alice.

981
01:22:30,720 --> 01:22:33,917
My kid sister used
to holler at me after school.

982
01:22:34,520 --> 01:22:38,069
She'd yell "Haaa-lice!"

983
01:22:42,000 --> 01:22:44,594
So they called me Hallie.

984
01:22:44,720 --> 01:22:46,950
Alice Martin.

985
01:22:49,760 --> 01:22:51,830
That fits you.

986
01:22:54,720 --> 01:22:56,711
I used to bite and pinch a lot too.

987
01:22:56,840 --> 01:22:58,637
I'll bet you did.

988
01:23:04,600 --> 01:23:09,230
It's mustangs. Mares.
They smell the horse.

989
01:23:19,080 --> 01:23:21,389
You know what you need?

990
01:23:25,200 --> 01:23:27,953
A pair of proper shoes.

991
01:23:35,200 --> 01:23:36,189
Hey.

992
01:23:38,760 --> 01:23:40,876
Where are we?

993
01:23:41,760 --> 01:23:43,716
Are we lost?

994
01:23:46,280 --> 01:23:48,236
Lost?

995
01:23:49,680 --> 01:23:51,238
No.

996
01:23:56,200 --> 01:23:59,033
Good night... Alice.

997
01:24:03,560 --> 01:24:05,949
Good night, Norman.

998
01:24:17,000 --> 01:24:20,549
If she's with Steele, then the network
will know where they are.

999
01:24:20,680 --> 01:24:23,035
That's the news department, Mr Sears.

1000
01:24:23,160 --> 01:24:26,516
I don't think they'll want
to give out that kind of information.

1001
01:24:26,640 --> 01:24:29,916
Are you saying we spent
$80 to $100 million in TV time...

1002
01:24:30,040 --> 01:24:32,429
...and we can't get
a simple piece of information?

1003
01:24:32,560 --> 01:24:35,916
- No, sir, I'm not saying that...
- You don't ask the news department.

1004
01:24:36,040 --> 01:24:39,271
Ask the advertising department.
They'll ask the news department.

1005
01:25:13,280 --> 01:25:15,510
What are you doin' up?

1006
01:25:16,840 --> 01:25:18,796
Nothing much.

1007
01:25:21,000 --> 01:25:25,039
You've had a hard day.
Why don't you scrunch down in the bag?

1008
01:25:27,400 --> 01:25:29,675
Oh, I wish it were that easy.

1009
01:25:30,360 --> 01:25:32,316
I don't sleep.

1010
01:25:33,320 --> 01:25:35,515
Ever?

1011
01:25:35,640 --> 01:25:37,870
How old are you?

1012
01:25:41,320 --> 01:25:44,995
Not in front of... in front
of people I don't know.

1013
01:25:48,440 --> 01:25:50,590
You slept last night.

1014
01:25:50,720 --> 01:25:52,870
The hell I did.

1015
01:25:57,640 --> 01:25:59,915
Not in front of a stranger.

1016
01:26:02,120 --> 01:26:06,079
What, are you afraid of what you'll
look like with your mouth open?

1017
01:26:09,080 --> 01:26:11,230
You have a mean streak in you.

1018
01:26:14,560 --> 01:26:16,232
No.

1019
01:26:17,360 --> 01:26:19,316
No, I don't.

1020
01:26:35,120 --> 01:26:37,395
I still pinch and bite.

1021
01:26:43,120 --> 01:26:44,872
OK.

1022
01:27:20,200 --> 01:27:22,156
Morning.

1023
01:27:25,160 --> 01:27:27,435
I'm still here.

1024
01:27:35,640 --> 01:27:40,839
There's... there's coffee from last night.
It's probably cold.

1025
01:27:42,680 --> 01:27:45,399
It probably is, if it hasn't been heated.

1026
01:27:46,840 --> 01:27:48,910
And there's cheese.

1027
01:27:50,560 --> 01:27:52,516
Cheese.

1028
01:27:55,200 --> 01:27:57,270
You're all bent. Are you sick?

1029
01:27:57,840 --> 01:27:59,956
No. Just bent.

1030
01:28:01,640 --> 01:28:04,518
Well... Here, have some cheese.

1031
01:28:05,240 --> 01:28:09,153
They say breakfast is the most
important meal of the day.

1032
01:28:10,000 --> 01:28:12,753
I know. I'm the one that said it.

1033
01:28:17,120 --> 01:28:20,078
- Are you sure you're not hurt?
- No. Just...

1034
01:28:20,200 --> 01:28:23,112
...some parts wake up faster than others.

1035
01:28:23,760 --> 01:28:26,433
Broke parts take a little longer, though.

1036
01:28:39,760 --> 01:28:42,354
I, uh, I would've called a cab,
left you a note.

1037
01:28:42,480 --> 01:28:45,756
You know, "Call me",
with my phone number.

1038
01:28:47,160 --> 01:28:51,119
Actually, I'd have left my answering
service number, just stuck it on the...

1039
01:28:51,240 --> 01:28:52,992
What's the matter?

1040
01:28:53,360 --> 01:28:55,715
I wanna know what's botherin' you.

1041
01:28:56,840 --> 01:29:01,470
It was just you and me last night.
It's not gonna be on television.

1042
01:29:05,200 --> 01:29:07,270
- Is it?
- I don't know what you mean.

1043
01:29:07,400 --> 01:29:11,871
The problem is you get up slowly, I get
up fast. It's... the way that I was raised.

1044
01:29:12,000 --> 01:29:15,879
- Hey, hey! I grew up gettin' up.
- We just got up, and got to work.

1045
01:29:16,000 --> 01:29:18,070
I was up before the sun
ever hit your room.

1046
01:29:18,200 --> 01:29:21,192
Well, then you get the getting-up medal.

1047
01:29:27,040 --> 01:29:30,669
Aren't we supposed to be in a hurry?
Isn't that what you said?

1048
01:29:30,960 --> 01:29:33,190
Good mornin', Alice.

1049
01:29:37,600 --> 01:29:39,716
Good morning.

1050
01:29:43,240 --> 01:29:45,629
You're right. We are in a hurry.

1051
01:29:46,480 --> 01:29:48,948
But let's say we lighten up a bit.

1052
01:29:49,440 --> 01:29:51,635
I think that's a great idea. Lighten up.

1053
01:29:51,760 --> 01:29:55,594
We're gonna be travelling together
a little while...

1054
01:30:00,520 --> 01:30:01,714
Oh...

1055
01:30:01,840 --> 01:30:04,149
There. All lightened up.

1056
01:30:13,760 --> 01:30:18,231
...<i>temperatures are dipping</i>
<i>below freezing in the high plateau</i>.

1057
01:30:18,360 --> 01:30:21,238
<i>On the national scene,</i>
<i>the search for Sonny Steele</i>...

1058
01:30:21,360 --> 01:30:25,399
...<i>is concentrated in central Utah</i>.
<i>KLSG switchboards have been jammed</i>...

1059
01:30:25,520 --> 01:30:28,717
- I didn't see any falls at Cisco Falls.
- There ain't any.

1060
01:30:28,840 --> 01:30:31,513
Hell, you can name anything anything.

1061
01:30:33,320 --> 01:30:36,357
It's like those people who
look up at the stars and see things.

1062
01:30:36,480 --> 01:30:40,393
Chickens and bulls and chariots
and snakes and shit...

1063
01:30:44,160 --> 01:30:48,119
What's this guy's name who's supposed
to have a belt? Ryan, or O'Ryan...

1064
01:30:48,240 --> 01:30:50,629
Hell, there ain't no belt up there.

1065
01:30:50,760 --> 01:30:53,399
Probably there was a falls here once.

1066
01:30:54,320 --> 01:30:57,437
This whole land was under water
millions of years ago.

1067
01:30:57,560 --> 01:31:02,793
If you go... if you go slow,
take your time and you look real close...

1068
01:31:02,920 --> 01:31:07,072
...you can find skeletons of these
weird-lookin' fishes in the hardpan...

1069
01:31:07,200 --> 01:31:09,395
...long, long gone.

1070
01:31:12,640 --> 01:31:16,952
All these mountains...
Hell, everything, everything you can see...

1071
01:31:17,560 --> 01:31:20,154
...everything, was under an ocean once.

1072
01:31:24,280 --> 01:31:28,398
- What are you smilin' at?
- I'm just enjoying the fact that you...

1073
01:31:29,000 --> 01:31:31,833
...that you know all that. It's interesting.

1074
01:31:33,720 --> 01:31:36,280
Well, this country's where I live.

1075
01:31:36,400 --> 01:31:39,870
- Don't you know where the subways go?
- Not lately.

1076
01:31:41,320 --> 01:31:43,231
Oh, yeah, you do.

1077
01:31:43,880 --> 01:31:45,871
How'd you know to find me?

1078
01:31:46,000 --> 01:31:49,595
Musta been 70, 80 reporters there,
but you were the one that found me.

1079
01:31:49,720 --> 01:31:52,712
Just had a few hunches
and got a head start.

1080
01:31:53,640 --> 01:31:57,952
Oh, you had more than that, Alice.
You are good.

1081
01:32:10,040 --> 01:32:11,996
Let's go.

1082
01:32:14,000 --> 01:32:16,070
Here, give me that stuff here.

1083
01:32:16,200 --> 01:32:19,476
OK, I want you to put
your left foot right here.

1084
01:32:19,600 --> 01:32:21,591
- Come on.
- I don't know how to ride.

1085
01:32:21,720 --> 01:32:24,473
You're not gonna ride.
I'm gonna be doin' the steering.

1086
01:32:24,600 --> 01:32:27,592
Listen, I'm not interested in horses.
They're... too big.

1087
01:32:27,720 --> 01:32:30,234
Hey, he ain't got a mean bone in his body.

1088
01:32:30,360 --> 01:32:34,797
We're not gonna get anywhere
with you in them spiky shoes. Come on.

1089
01:32:35,800 --> 01:32:38,997
- Oh, God...
- OK, swing your right leg right on over.

1090
01:32:39,120 --> 01:32:41,315
That's it. There you go.

1091
01:32:41,760 --> 01:32:43,716
Here.

1092
01:32:43,920 --> 01:32:47,435
- Uh, should I pet him?
- Do what you want. He ain't no dog.

1093
01:32:58,400 --> 01:33:01,437
<i> Doyle Hicks</i>.
<i>Go ahead, you're on the air</i>.

1094
01:33:01,560 --> 01:33:04,074
- <i> Is this Doyle?</i>
- <i>Turn down your radio</i>.

1095
01:33:04,200 --> 01:33:07,237
<i>Yeah, well, I just wanna say</i>
<i>that what Sonny Steele done</i>...

1096
01:33:07,360 --> 01:33:10,272
...<i>is wonderful news</i>
<i>for the animals of this country</i>.

1097
01:33:10,400 --> 01:33:14,791
<i> If somebody's poisoning an</i>
<i>animal, a person should try and stop it</i>.

1098
01:33:14,920 --> 01:33:17,480
<i> I'd have done</i>
<i>the same damn thing myself</i>.

1099
01:33:17,600 --> 01:33:21,559
<i>Them Ampco people</i>
<i>got no right to dope up a horse</i>.

1100
01:33:51,640 --> 01:33:54,234
- What you got?
- Not gonna throw this away, are you?

1101
01:33:54,360 --> 01:33:55,475
- What is it?
- Just notes.

1102
01:33:55,600 --> 01:33:57,318
Can I see 'em?

1103
01:33:57,440 --> 01:33:59,590
They're just my notes.

1104
01:34:02,120 --> 01:34:04,839
- What are these, in Russian?
- That's my handwriting.

1105
01:34:04,960 --> 01:34:07,110
- Well, read 'em.
- No.

1106
01:34:08,680 --> 01:34:10,875
You got a secret?

1107
01:34:18,080 --> 01:34:22,232
"I feel I'm seeing this country
for the first time."

1108
01:34:23,400 --> 01:34:26,949
"Not looking down
from a jet 30,000ft up...

1109
01:34:27,080 --> 01:34:32,950
...but from the low angle... of a special
man who means to cross it on foot...

1110
01:34:33,080 --> 01:34:38,359
...leading a thoroughbred stallion to
a secret destination... to a private goal."

1111
01:34:39,680 --> 01:34:43,958
"To a fairness that he intends
to find in these valleys."

1112
01:34:45,480 --> 01:34:49,598
"I..." I can't. They're just my notes.
I'm embarrassed.

1113
01:34:58,920 --> 01:35:00,672
Nice.

1114
01:35:01,160 --> 01:35:03,958
- It's hype.
- Coulda fooled me.

1115
01:35:07,040 --> 01:35:09,873
She ordered a camera crew
to meet her at Rim Rock Canyon.

1116
01:35:10,000 --> 01:35:13,549
- I suppose to photograph the...
- The ceremony.

1117
01:35:13,680 --> 01:35:16,148
The sales figures again, exactly.

1118
01:35:17,040 --> 01:35:21,511
In the three days since he took the horse,
office equipment has been as projected...

1119
01:35:21,640 --> 01:35:23,551
The cereal.

1120
01:35:23,680 --> 01:35:25,989
Cumulatively, up 30 per cent.

1121
01:35:26,520 --> 01:35:30,274
And by closing time today
they'd emptied the shelves.

1122
01:35:35,120 --> 01:35:36,997
Yes, Fitzgerald, what is it?

1123
01:35:37,120 --> 01:35:42,353
Well, sir, there's something here
that I think you should be aware of.

1124
01:35:46,720 --> 01:35:50,235
- Where'd you get that?
- There are kids selling 'em on the street.

1125
01:35:52,000 --> 01:35:54,389
Now that's not supposed to be there.

1126
01:35:54,520 --> 01:35:56,750
Or we're not supposed to be here.

1127
01:35:56,880 --> 01:35:58,836
<i>You're</i> lost?

1128
01:36:00,240 --> 01:36:03,789
About a mile's worth, I'd say.
We gotta get off this ridge.

1129
01:36:04,640 --> 01:36:06,596
Maybe... Do...

1130
01:36:06,960 --> 01:36:11,556
- Maybe I could get us some supplies.
- We got enough supplies. Let's go.

1131
01:36:14,280 --> 01:36:15,474
Oh!

1132
01:36:17,960 --> 01:36:19,916
Here, here...

1133
01:36:20,040 --> 01:36:21,996
You OK?

1134
01:36:22,960 --> 01:36:24,632
Are you all right?

1135
01:36:24,760 --> 01:36:26,830
A- OK.

1136
01:36:26,960 --> 01:36:30,475
- You sure?
- Yeah. Let's go.

1137
01:36:31,120 --> 01:36:32,792
Maybe you ought to sit down.

1138
01:36:32,920 --> 01:36:37,869
- You don't understand the problem.
- Well, lay down or somethin'. Here.

1139
01:36:38,000 --> 01:36:40,514
And listen to you bitch about my boots?
No, thank you.

1140
01:36:40,640 --> 01:36:43,552
No, no. I'm beginnin' to like 'em.
Here. Right here.

1141
01:36:43,680 --> 01:36:45,989
Oh... God, my back.

1142
01:36:46,680 --> 01:36:48,272
Easy.

1143
01:36:48,560 --> 01:36:50,516
Let's take a look.

1144
01:36:50,920 --> 01:36:54,515
You just relax, cos we're makin'
good time, don't worry.

1145
01:36:55,840 --> 01:36:57,796
Hold on.

1146
01:37:10,080 --> 01:37:11,433
Here.

1147
01:37:11,560 --> 01:37:12,629
Oh.

1148
01:37:12,760 --> 01:37:14,671
Little hair of the dog.

1149
01:37:14,800 --> 01:37:16,233
Oh!

1150
01:37:24,440 --> 01:37:28,194
- I feel better already.
- Yeah, well, don't put it away.

1151
01:37:35,520 --> 01:37:41,038
Hey, why don't you get some rest?
I'll go find us a place to cross the road.

1152
01:37:42,280 --> 01:37:44,236
I won't be long.

1153
01:37:51,360 --> 01:37:53,635
Hi, there. What's your name?

1154
01:37:54,320 --> 01:37:57,278
- Louise.
- Oh! Same as mine.

1155
01:37:58,280 --> 01:38:02,671
You, uh... you taking care
of this place all by yourself?

1156
01:38:02,800 --> 01:38:07,351
- Is your name really Louise?
- You bet. Your mom and dad here?

1157
01:38:07,480 --> 01:38:10,313
My mom went to get butane.
We're all out.

1158
01:38:11,000 --> 01:38:13,036
- You have a telephone?
- It's out too.

1159
01:38:13,160 --> 01:38:17,711
Every time it snows up at Marysville,
first thing, the phone goes out.

1160
01:38:17,840 --> 01:38:19,796
Where's your car?

1161
01:38:20,400 --> 01:38:24,393
Oh, I'm... I'm sort of camping out,
and my car went on the blink.

1162
01:38:24,520 --> 01:38:27,910
And I, uh... I need
to get a message to my boss.

1163
01:38:28,040 --> 01:38:30,998
Are you gonna be near a phone later on?
After you close up?

1164
01:38:31,120 --> 01:38:32,838
Well, we got a phone at home.

1165
01:38:32,960 --> 01:38:35,474
I bet you could call for me
and get a message to him.

1166
01:38:35,600 --> 01:38:39,115
Could you do that? How much
do you charge to make a call?

1167
01:38:39,240 --> 01:38:40,798
One dollar.

1168
01:38:40,920 --> 01:38:43,878
That's fair. OK, let me
give you the phone number...

1169
01:38:44,000 --> 01:38:48,118
...and when you get him on the phone, ask
for Les Charles. Don't talk to anybody else.

1170
01:38:48,240 --> 01:38:50,356
And tell him you're calling for me...

1171
01:38:50,480 --> 01:38:52,994
- For Louise.
- No... Yeah.

1172
01:38:53,120 --> 01:38:55,759
- Louise, in Utah.
- I know what state it is.

1173
01:38:55,880 --> 01:39:01,716
Tell him I said call off the crew, call off
everything. I'll explain when I see him.

1174
01:39:01,840 --> 01:39:05,071
- Shouldn't I say your car broke down?
- No, no. Just the rest of it.

1175
01:39:05,200 --> 01:39:09,034
- About the flu?
- No, the <i>crew</i>. I'll write it out for you.

1176
01:39:09,160 --> 01:39:11,799
- Her car broke down.
- Oh, where's it at, miss?

1177
01:39:11,920 --> 01:39:13,956
Well, it...

1178
01:39:14,080 --> 01:39:16,719
Well, it didn't really break down,
it's just acting...

1179
01:39:16,840 --> 01:39:18,910
And I have to call her boss about it.

1180
01:39:19,040 --> 01:39:22,874
Say, aren't you... You know, television.
You've seen her.

1181
01:39:23,000 --> 01:39:26,037
- Last week I saw her.
- News. News. News commentator.

1182
01:39:26,160 --> 01:39:29,470
It's too complicated, Louise.
Thanks anyway.

1183
01:39:30,520 --> 01:39:33,273
- What's your name? Please.
- Louise.

1184
01:39:36,760 --> 01:39:38,910
Found us a spot.

1185
01:39:40,640 --> 01:39:43,359
- How you doin'?
- Good as new.

1186
01:39:44,120 --> 01:39:46,076
Serves you right.

1187
01:39:48,600 --> 01:39:51,672
There's a place we can cross the road
about a mile south.

1188
01:39:51,800 --> 01:39:56,430
Gotta honk on it though.
I wanna get there before dark.

1189
01:39:56,920 --> 01:39:58,433
We're that close?

1190
01:39:58,560 --> 01:40:02,269
Yeah, for where we can spend the night.
Inside, for a change. Come on.

1191
01:40:02,400 --> 01:40:06,678
Isn't there some closer place where
you guys take horses to let 'em go?

1192
01:40:06,800 --> 01:40:09,553
No. I just usually use the one, myself.

1193
01:40:10,640 --> 01:40:13,632
It's so pretty here.
If I were Rising Star, I'd love to...

1194
01:40:13,760 --> 01:40:15,637
Well, you're not. Come on.

1195
01:40:15,760 --> 01:40:19,992
Do me a favour, will you, Alice?
Don't go tryin' to think like a horse.

1196
01:40:20,880 --> 01:40:22,916
I'll worry about him. You just take notes.

1197
01:40:38,480 --> 01:40:43,474
OI' Clark Wembly had this place built.
Us cowboys used to use it for huntin'.

1198
01:40:43,600 --> 01:40:47,115
Now Clark Wembly... was really somethin'.

1199
01:40:47,760 --> 01:40:51,514
He had a voice that was
just like runnin' molasses.

1200
01:40:52,320 --> 01:40:56,359
And it'd come over the PA system...
"Sorry you lost, Sonny."

1201
01:40:56,480 --> 01:41:00,439
And there I'd be, lyin' in the dirt, just
havin' been dumped on by some bull...

1202
01:41:00,560 --> 01:41:04,792
...just broke and busted, but ol' Clark's
voice'd come sailin' across...

1203
01:41:04,920 --> 01:41:09,118
...and he'd say "Give him a big hand, folks.
Glad you come. Better luck next time."

1204
01:41:09,240 --> 01:41:11,754
God, Jesus! He was so terrific.

1205
01:41:12,240 --> 01:41:15,437
He made me feel good.
He made me feel like tryin'.

1206
01:41:15,560 --> 01:41:20,236
And he had a big bay mare outta Idaho.
Oh, what an animal.

1207
01:41:20,360 --> 01:41:22,510
That horse used to ju...

1208
01:41:24,240 --> 01:41:27,949
Bub-bub-blurgh-blurgh,
runnin' right off at the mouth.

1209
01:41:28,600 --> 01:41:30,556
I enjoyed it.

1210
01:41:37,000 --> 01:41:41,152
- When are we gonna get there?
- About midday.

1211
01:41:47,920 --> 01:41:49,876
It's been a long haul.

1212
01:41:59,000 --> 01:42:01,275
Somethin' bothering you?

1213
01:42:03,200 --> 01:42:07,671
- What are you gonna do after?
- Oh, you gonna start with the questions?

1214
01:42:08,280 --> 01:42:14,435
Well, when he's loose, chasing mares,
do you just... do you just do the same?

1215
01:42:15,640 --> 01:42:17,915
What do <i>you</i> think?

1216
01:42:18,040 --> 01:42:22,591
You're the one takin' the notes.
You're a... clever lady.

1217
01:42:22,960 --> 01:42:26,953
- What do you think's gonna happen?
- You say it like it's a bad word, "clever".

1218
01:42:27,080 --> 01:42:29,310
No. I like you bein' smart.

1219
01:42:30,720 --> 01:42:35,157
It's just sometimes you're so busy
being clever that I don't...

1220
01:42:36,640 --> 01:42:39,552
When was the last time
you were surprised?

1221
01:42:41,680 --> 01:42:43,636
You.

1222
01:42:44,160 --> 01:42:46,276
You were a surprise.

1223
01:42:54,760 --> 01:42:56,751
I told them.

1224
01:42:56,880 --> 01:42:58,871
Wha... Who?

1225
01:43:00,120 --> 01:43:01,917
I, uh...

1226
01:43:06,400 --> 01:43:10,916
I called the network and I told them
you were going to Rim Rock Canyon.

1227
01:43:11,040 --> 01:43:14,555
And I asked them to meet me there
with a camera crew.

1228
01:43:15,720 --> 01:43:17,278
Oh.

1229
01:43:19,560 --> 01:43:21,357
And that's not all.

1230
01:43:21,840 --> 01:43:24,149
Oh, now for the <i>bad</i> news?

1231
01:43:25,600 --> 01:43:29,832
I lied when I said I was gonna go to jail.
I wasn't in any trouble.

1232
01:43:35,120 --> 01:43:36,599
Well.

1233
01:43:37,800 --> 01:43:40,189
Well, well, well.

1234
01:43:45,280 --> 01:43:47,396
What <i>do</i> you know.

1235
01:43:48,320 --> 01:43:51,915
Oh, Sonny... Please, don't just walk away.

1236
01:43:52,040 --> 01:43:55,191
Don't be like that. Hit me,
yell at me, slap me or something.

1237
01:43:55,320 --> 01:43:57,675
I already slapped you.
First time we was alone.

1238
01:43:57,800 --> 01:44:02,396
- Swear to God I wouldn't do it now.
- Oh? Is that right? You a new person?

1239
01:44:02,520 --> 01:44:04,954
It was three days ago.
I didn't understand what...

1240
01:44:05,080 --> 01:44:07,469
Yeah. A lot can happen in three days.

1241
01:44:08,920 --> 01:44:11,832
I didn't want to ruin anything for you,
Sonny.

1242
01:44:11,960 --> 01:44:16,033
- I had a job to do and I wanted a story.
- Well, you got it.

1243
01:44:16,640 --> 01:44:18,596
You did it.

1244
01:44:27,560 --> 01:44:29,710
Hey, how about my letter?

1245
01:44:30,960 --> 01:44:33,679
Did you mail it?
Or is that gonna be on TV?

1246
01:44:33,800 --> 01:44:35,756
Oh, please!

1247
01:44:40,440 --> 01:44:43,159
- Well, what are you gonna do?
- What I said.

1248
01:44:43,280 --> 01:44:46,033
- Why not just take him to another place?
- No.

1249
01:44:46,280 --> 01:44:48,840
- Why?
- I want him at <i>that</i> place.

1250
01:44:48,960 --> 01:44:51,952
Everybody's done their thing.
Ampco did what they had to do...

1251
01:44:52,080 --> 01:44:54,196
...you did, now I'm gonna do
what I have to do.

1252
01:44:54,320 --> 01:44:57,835
Sonny, you can't go there.
They'll be there. The police may be there.

1253
01:44:57,960 --> 01:45:01,714
I can't run for ever. Look, we're either
all goin' to heaven or we ain't.

1254
01:45:01,840 --> 01:45:05,435
Besides, you want to see the finish.
Well, be still.

1255
01:45:06,520 --> 01:45:08,476
Let it finish.

1256
01:45:10,600 --> 01:45:13,068
Oh, I don't want you to be hurt.

1257
01:45:13,960 --> 01:45:16,554
I've been hurt. I still get up.

1258
01:45:24,320 --> 01:45:26,470
Thanks for the worry.

1259
01:45:31,480 --> 01:45:33,596
Do me a favour?

1260
01:45:33,720 --> 01:45:36,757
Tomorrow... don't take notes.

1261
01:45:39,360 --> 01:45:41,555
Oh, Sonny, I'm so sorry.

1262
01:46:17,320 --> 01:46:19,470
Better get off.

1263
01:46:24,440 --> 01:46:26,908
How soon before we get there?

1264
01:46:29,960 --> 01:46:32,155
We <i>are</i> there.

1265
01:46:36,880 --> 01:46:39,872
Wait a minute...
The camera crew, they're not here.

1266
01:46:41,680 --> 01:46:43,477
Appears not.

1267
01:46:43,600 --> 01:46:46,637
Well, Star, what do you think of the place?

1268
01:46:47,120 --> 01:46:49,759
They... they must be at another entrance.

1269
01:46:49,880 --> 01:46:52,075
Ain't no other entrance.

1270
01:46:53,600 --> 01:46:55,750
Well, then hurry. Maybe they're lost.

1271
01:46:55,880 --> 01:46:58,030
I doubt it.

1272
01:46:58,960 --> 01:47:00,916
Well, where the hell are they?

1273
01:47:01,040 --> 01:47:04,635
Probably in Rim Rock Canyon.
Isn't that where you told 'em to go?

1274
01:47:07,960 --> 01:47:10,349
They'd be about 90 miles north.

1275
01:47:11,480 --> 01:47:15,553
- This isn't...
- This here's Silver Reef. Pretty, ain't it?

1276
01:47:16,920 --> 01:47:17,557
You...

1277
01:47:17,680 --> 01:47:21,150
Oh, no, now! I never said we were goin'
to no Rim Rock Canyon! You said it!

1278
01:47:21,280 --> 01:47:24,078
Hey, look out!
Don't get me with them boots!

1279
01:47:26,520 --> 01:47:28,829
Where is he?
And what was this about a reward?

1280
01:47:28,960 --> 01:47:31,349
- I... I...
- We've been misinformed.

1281
01:47:31,480 --> 01:47:34,119
When our own investigation
revealed the truth...

1282
01:47:34,240 --> 01:47:36,913
...naturally we understood
Mr Steele's motivation.

1283
01:47:40,080 --> 01:47:44,039
I don't think there's enough food
to last another night.

1284
01:47:46,640 --> 01:47:49,757
- I don't think he's coming.
- It's occurred to me.

1285
01:47:55,800 --> 01:47:59,315
Well, Star, you wanna
say goodbye to the lady?

1286
01:48:03,800 --> 01:48:05,756
Hey, boy.

1287
01:48:11,440 --> 01:48:13,829
- Swing your tail.
- Excuse us.

1288
01:48:25,200 --> 01:48:26,952
OK.

1289
01:48:28,080 --> 01:48:31,914
Remember, they're just horses.
Same as you.

1290
01:48:32,720 --> 01:48:36,759
Only they've never been broke. But
they ain't won no championships neither.

1291
01:48:39,440 --> 01:48:42,796
So when you cross that stallion
and he wants to fight...

1292
01:48:42,920 --> 01:48:47,789
...you remember, you got the blood
on your side. And you can take him.

1293
01:48:50,120 --> 01:48:53,271
- Is he just gonna go, just like that?
- You bet.

1294
01:48:53,920 --> 01:48:56,718
- I thought you guys were pals.
- We are.

1295
01:49:01,640 --> 01:49:04,029
Make somethin' outta yourself now.

1296
01:49:59,360 --> 01:50:01,999
Yeah. When I see you, Les.
About nine o'clock.

1297
01:50:02,120 --> 01:50:04,076
OK, bye-bye.

1298
01:50:08,880 --> 01:50:12,156
There's your bus. Looks like it's on time.

1299
01:50:12,560 --> 01:50:14,630
Oh. Good.

1300
01:50:20,240 --> 01:50:22,629
- How do you feel?
- I feel good.

1301
01:50:23,800 --> 01:50:26,439
Maybe not as good as him, but... good.

1302
01:50:26,560 --> 01:50:28,471
What did they say?

1303
01:50:28,600 --> 01:50:33,071
Oh, they're full of congratulations.
Can't wait to get the story.

1304
01:50:33,200 --> 01:50:36,829
Especially now that Ampco
has reversed its position.

1305
01:50:36,960 --> 01:50:38,439
Yeah, I'll bet.

1306
01:50:38,560 --> 01:50:42,314
They have me going to Paris next
to cover the elections.

1307
01:50:42,840 --> 01:50:46,594
Well, no kiddin'?
That oughta be interesting.

1308
01:50:49,120 --> 01:50:52,874
- More coffee?
- No, not for me, thanks. You want any?

1309
01:50:53,600 --> 01:50:55,238
Yes, please.

1310
01:50:57,440 --> 01:51:00,318
Just a little somethin' for the road.

1311
01:51:16,800 --> 01:51:19,439
Ho, ho, ho... Careful there.

1312
01:51:31,840 --> 01:51:32,875
Tell me, Norman...

1313
01:51:33,000 --> 01:51:36,515
...did you think it'd be this tough
to get rid of a pain in the ass like me?

1314
01:51:37,560 --> 01:51:39,391
Ma'am, I had no idea.

1315
01:51:39,520 --> 01:51:44,150
All aboard the bus. Cedar City,
Richfield, Utah, and Denver, Colorado.

1316
01:51:49,720 --> 01:51:52,598
Uh, that story you're gonna tell...

1317
01:51:52,720 --> 01:51:56,110
It'd be nice if you didn't mention
where it was that we let him go.

1318
01:51:56,240 --> 01:51:57,673
Silver Reef?

1319
01:51:57,800 --> 01:52:00,268
Be nice if you didn't divulge <i>that</i> source.

1320
01:52:00,400 --> 01:52:03,437
I don't know, leave out a name like that...

1321
01:52:09,680 --> 01:52:12,353
What are you gonna do tomorrow, Sonny?

1322
01:52:12,840 --> 01:52:15,912
Oh, I'm gonna... get movin' on.

1323
01:52:17,480 --> 01:52:19,755
Find me somethin' simple.

1324
01:52:21,720 --> 01:52:25,235
Hard, maybe, but plain and quiet.

1325
01:52:26,560 --> 01:52:28,551
Any bags, ma'am?

1326
01:52:28,680 --> 01:52:30,432
Uh, no.

1327
01:52:32,920 --> 01:52:34,672
Uh, hey...?

1328
01:52:36,400 --> 01:52:38,675
I keep wantin' to thank you.

1329
01:52:38,800 --> 01:52:41,234
But then I keep wonderin' what for.

1330
01:52:41,800 --> 01:52:44,030
I know. I know. Me too.

1331
01:52:46,600 --> 01:52:51,515
Maybe it's for how I'm gonna feel
whenever I see you on television.

1332
01:52:55,240 --> 01:52:58,073
Guess I'm gonna have to get me a TV.

1333
01:53:02,400 --> 01:53:03,913
So...

1334
01:53:04,040 --> 01:53:05,996
All aboard, ma'am.

1335
01:53:15,280 --> 01:53:17,840
- So long, Alice.
- So long, Norman.

1336
01:53:18,840 --> 01:53:21,035
Have a safe trip back now.

1337
01:53:34,920 --> 01:53:37,514
All charges have been dropped,
and, sources say...

1338
01:53:37,640 --> 01:53:41,633
...the Ampco art department
